<refsect1>
<title>Getting Gegl from CVS on Unix-like Systems</title>

<para>
Gegl is available from the gnome CVS site. You can get it through anonymous
CVS. To access the tree you need to first set up your CVSROOT enviroment variable 
so that CVS knows where to go to grab the source from. 
</para>

<para>
The following interactive bash shell commands shows how to get it from anonymous CVS:
<programlisting>
$ export CVSROOT=':pserver:anonymous@anoncvs.gnome.org:/cvs/gnome'
$ cvs login
</programlisting>
</para>

<para>
This will ask you for a password. There is no password so just enter a carriage
return. To get the tree and place it in a subdir of your current working
directory, issue the command:
<programlisting>
$ cvs -z3 checkout gegl
</programlisting>
</para>

<para>
Next you are ready to configure and compile Gegl.
</para>

